proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

premint((address,string,string,address[].notice: Creates a new token on the given erc1155 contract on behalf of a creator, and mints x tokens to the executor of this transaction. If a premintCollection parameter is provided, it will execute the premint against the collection at that address. If the premintCollection parameter is not provided, it will get or create an 1155 contract at a deterministic address using the contractConfig. The creator must sign the intent to create the token, and must have mint new token permission on the erc1155 contract, or match the contract admin on the contract creation config if the contract hasn't been created yet. Contract address of the created contract is deterministically generated from the contract config and this contract's address.
